  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    EventListener, javax.faces.component.PartialStateHolder, javax.faces.component.StateHolder, javax.faces.component.TransientStateHolder, javax.faces.event.ComponentSystemEventListener, javax.faces.event.FacesListener, javax.faces.event.SystemEventListenerHolder

    public class RichSuggestionsSection
extends org.apache.myfaces.trinidad.component.UIXObject
    The component manages a list of preferred suggestions based on various factors on the client. The parent inputSearch component retrieves the list managed by this component and displays it in UI. The preferred suggestions list managed by this component is a subset of the suggestions retrieved via the REST service. Implementation Details:
    • Ordering of suggestions in the UI is implementation specific. The current implementation scores the suggestions based on recency, number of times the suggestions item is selected and time based decay.
    • The preferred suggestions list represented by af:suggestionsSection may not be displayed by af:inputSearch component if the master list of suggestions managed by af:inputSerch is small. Determining if the master list is small is an implementation detail.
    • Determining the master list length is small could lag e.g. the first time the suggestions popup is launched, the master list length will be determined, and in such cases, the preferred suggestions list will displayed even if the suggestions list length is small.

    Values    		 Event delivered to describe an attribute change. Attribute change events are not delivered for any programmatic change to a property. They are only delivered when a renderer changes a property without the application's specific request. An example of an attribute change event might include the width of a column that supported client-side resizing.

      • getCacheKeyGenerator

        public final String getCacheKeyGenerator()
        Gets The attribute holds the name of a JS function. The return value of this function will be used as the key for client storage. The normalized URL of the default searchSection is passed as a parameter to the function, and the function's "this" keyword will refer to the parent inputSearch component instance.

        Sample JS method:

        function privateList(normalizedUrl)
         {
           // "this" refers to parent inputSearch component
           return this.getClientId();
         }
        Returns:
        the new cacheKeyGenerator value
